documentation.text: @notice Returns all the relevant information about a specific kitty.

devdoc.author: Axiom Zen (https://www.axiomzen.co)
devdoc.details: The main CryptoKitties contract, keeps track of kittens so they don't wander around and get lost.

params._to: The address to be granted transfer approval. Pass address(0) to  clear all approvals.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

createGen0Auction(string,address).details: Creates a new gen0 kitty with the given genes and  creates an auction for it.

createSaleAuction(uint256,uint256,uint25.details: Put a kitty up for auction.  Does some ownership trickery to create auctions in one tx.

pause().details: Called by any "C-level" role to pause the contract. Used only when  a bug or exploit is detected and we need to limit damage.

setCEO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the CEO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCEO: The address of the new CEO

setCFO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the CFO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCFO: The address of the new CFO

setCOO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the COO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCOO: The address of the new COO

setMetadataAddress(address).details: Set the address of the sibling contract that tracks metadata.  CEO only.

setNewAddress(address).details: Used to mark the smart contract as upgraded, in case there is a serious  breaking bug. This method does nothing but keep track of the new contract and  emit a message indicating that the new address is set. It's up to clients of this  contract to update to the new contract address in that case. (This contract will  be paused indefinitely if such an upgrade takes place.)

setSaleAuctionAddress(address).details: Sets the reference to the sale auction.

params._tokenId: The ID number of the Kitty whose metadata should be returned.

tokensOfOwner(address).details: This method MUST NEVER be called by smart contract code. First, it's fairly  expensive (it walks the entire Kitty array looking for cats belonging to owner),  but it also returns a dynamic array, which is only supported for web3 calls, and  not contract-to-contract calls.

params._owner: The owner whose Kitties we are interested in.

params._to: The address of the recipient, can be a user or contract.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty to transfer.

params._from: The address that owns the Kitty to be transfered.
params._to: The address that should take ownership of the Kitty. Can be any address,  including the caller.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty to be transferred.

unpause().details: Override unpause so it requires all external contract addresses  to be set before contract can be unpaused. Also, we can't have  newContractAddress set either, because then the contract was upgraded.

withdrawAuctionBalances().details: Transfers the balance of the sale auction contract to the KittyCore contract. We use two-step withdrawal to prevent two transfer calls in the auction bid function.

devdoc.title: CryptoKitties: Collectible, breedable, and oh-so-adorable cats on the Ethereum blockchain.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Grant another address the right to transfer a specific Kitty via  transferFrom(). This is the preferred flow for transfering NFTs to contracts.

balanceOf(address).notice: Returns the number of Kitties owned by a specific address.

getChamp(uint32).notice: Returns all the relevant information about a specific kitty.

name().notice: Name and symbol of the non fungible token, as defined in ERC721.

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Returns the address currently assigned ownership of a given Kitty.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Introspection interface as per ERC-165 (https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/165).  Returns true for any standardized interfaces implemented by this contract. We implement  ERC-165 (obviously!) and ERC-721.

tokenMetadata(uint256,string).notice: Returns a URI pointing to a metadata package for this token conforming to  ERC-721 (https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/721)

tokensOfOwner(address).notice: Returns a list of all Kitty IDs assigned to an address.

totalSupply().notice: Returns the total number of Kitties currently in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers a Kitty to another address. If transferring to a smart  contract be VERY CAREFUL to ensure that it is aware of ERC-721 (or  CryptoKitties specifically) or your Kitty may be lost forever. Seriously.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer a Kitty owned by another address, for which the calling address  has previously been granted transfer approval by the owner.

unpause().notice: This is public rather than external so we can call super.unpause  without using an expensive CALL.
